</figure>

<h2>Some fun things I did were:</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Dynamically load only the current and past day’s content into the page (server-side, so no peeking!)</li>
  <li>Only allow the window of the current day to open and show the lightbox with content in. <small>[Edit] this has been changed at the request of <em>The Bouse</em> now Christmas is over</small></li>
  <li>Change the theme to night after 5pm (dark sky, different coloured logos)</li>
  <li>CSS 3D transforms to open the calendar windows</li>
  <li><a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-transforms/#perspective-property">CSS Perspective</a> on the calendar to allow the calendar windows to peek open at different angles</li>
  <li>A little bit of Modernizr to help cope with legacy browsers!</li>
  <li>Falling snow! Courtesy of <a href="http://www.schillmania.com/projects/snowstorm">Mr Scott Schiller</a></li>
  <li>Dynamic favicon based on the day! Kudos to <a href="http://remysharp.com/2010/08/24/dynamic-favicons">Remy Sharp for the initial idea on this</a></li>
</ul>

